		"description": "<p>At 6th level, you gain resistance to necrotic damage.</p>\n<p>Additionally, as part of your movement you may briefly step into the Ethereal Plane, enabling you to move through other creatures and objects as if they were difficult terrain. You cannot attack or be attacked while you are incorporeal in this fashion. If you end your turn inside an object, you take 1d10 force damage and are immediately shunted into an adjacent square. You may remain in the Ethereal Plane for a number of consecutive rounds equal to your Constitution modifier. Once you have used this ability, you may not do so again until you complete a long rest.</p>",
